The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in South Africa is currently at 73 533. 1 148 933 tests have been conducted cumulatively with a total of 26 975 new tests conducted in the last 24 hours. A further 88 COVID-19 deaths have been reported: 73 from the Western Cape, 9 from the Eastern Cape, and 6 from Gauteng Province. This brings the total national death toll to 1568 with a mortality rate of 2.1%. The recoveries to date are 39 867- this translates to a recovery rate of 54.2%. 